1. WHAT IS FIREBASE? (quick overview)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Firebase is Google's app development platform. The parts we use here:

  Cloud Functions    — backend code that runs in response to events
  Realtime Database  — a NoSQL cloud database (JSON tree)
  Cloud Storage      — file storage (images, etc.)
  Firebase Auth      — user authentication
  Cloud PubSub       — message queues & scheduled tasks

Instead of managing a server, you write small function files.
Firebase calls them when something happens (HTTP request, DB write, file upload, etc.)

