2. FIREBASE CONCEPTS FOR THIS PROJECT
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

a) Cloud Functions — 3 types:

   HTTP functions     functions.https.onRequest
                      Like a regular Express route. Client sends HTTP request, function runs.
                      Used for: CRUD endpoints (create, read, update, delete blog posts)

   Callable functions functions.https.onCall
                      Like HTTP but Firebase automatically passes auth context (user ID).
                      Client calls it with the Firebase SDK, not curl/Postman.
                      Used for: upvote, downvote (need auth + simple input)

   Background triggers
     Auth trigger     functions.auth.user().onCreate
                      Runs when a new user signs up. Used to create user profile in DB.

     DB trigger       functions.database.ref("/path/{id}").onCreate
                      Runs when data is written to a DB path. Used to count views, votes.

     Storage trigger  functions.storage.object().onFinalize
                      Runs when a file is uploaded. Used to resize images.

     PubSub trigger   functions.pubsub.schedule("cron").onRun
                      Runs on a timer (cron schedule). Used for daily reports.

b) Realtime Database (RTDB):

   Data is stored as a JSON tree:
   {
     "posts": {
       "-abc123": { "title": "...", "text": "...", ... },
       "-def456": { ... }
     },
     "votes": { ... },
     "readReceipts": { ... },
     "profiles": { ... },
     "reports": { ... }
   }

   Each post gets a unique key like "-abc123" (auto-generated by push()).

   Access patterns:
     ref("posts").once("value")                    → get all posts
     ref("posts").orderByChild("title").once("value") → query with filter
     ref("posts/-abc123").once("value")             → get single post
     ref("posts").push({...})                       → create new post
     ref("posts/-abc123").update({...})             → update post
     ref("posts/-abc123").remove()                  → delete post

c) Firebase Admin SDK:

   admin.initializeApp()         — initialize Firebase in the backend
   admin.auth().verifyIdToken()  — verify user token from client
   admin.credential.cert()        — authenticate with service account

   These are already set up in defaultApp.ts — you don't need to touch them.

d) This repo's file conventions:

   - Each Cloud Function goes in src/CloudFunctions/cfXxx.ts
   - DB read logic goes in src/DataAccess/Read/getXxx.ts
   - DB write logic goes in src/DataAccess/Write/setXxx.ts
   - Validation logic goes in src/Validators/
   - All Cloud Functions are exported from src/index.ts
   - Function names: prefix with "cf" (e.g. cfCreatePost, cfUpvote)
   - Default app (admin + DB) is imported from Helpers/defaultApp

