6. HOW TO TEST EVERYTHING
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

a) Start the emulators:
  cd functions
  npm run serve

b) Test HTTP endpoints with curl:

  Create a post:
    curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5001/ssrtest-cebd9/us-central1/createPost \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -H "Authorization: Bearer owner" \
      -d '{"title":"My First Post","text":"Hello world!","category":"tech"}'

  Get all posts:
    curl http://127.0.0.1:5001/ssrtest-cebd9/us-central1/getPosts

  Get posts with filters:
    curl "http://127.0.0.1:5001/ssrtest-cebd9/us-central1/getPosts?category=tech&page=1&limit=5"

  Get a single post:
    curl http://127.0.0.1:5001/ssrtest-cebd9/us-central1/getPost \
      -H "Authorization: Bearer owner" \
      -d "{\"postId\":\"-abc123\"}"

  (For GET with a body, use Postman or write a small script.)

c) Test callable functions with Firebase Shell:
  npm run shell
  # Then in the shell:
  upvote({ postId: "-abc123" }, { auth: { uid: "test123" } })
  downvote({ postId: "-abc123" }, { auth: { uid: "test123" } })
  revokeVote({ postId: "-abc123" }, { auth: { uid: "test123" } })

d) Test auth trigger:
  In the emulator UI (http://127.0.0.1:4000/auth), create a new user.
  Check the database to see if a profile was created.

e) Test database triggers:
  Write directly to the database path in the emulator UI:
    /posts/newPost → write a test post → check if views/votes are set to 0
    /readReceipts/newPost/testUid → write true → check if post view incremented

f) Test storage trigger:
  Upload an image through the emulator Storage UI.
  Check if a resized version appears.

g) Test pubsub:
  In the Firebase Shell:
    pubsubDailyReport()
  Or wait for the scheduled time.

