GLOSSARY (for Firebase beginners)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  RTDB        Realtime Database — the JSON database
  uid         User ID — unique identifier for each user
  push()      Creates a new node with a unique auto-generated key
  once()       Reads data one time (not listening for changes)
  set()        Writes data to a path (overwrites everything at that path)
  update()     Writes specific fields without overwriting others
  remove()     Deletes data at a path
  transaction() Atomically read-modify-write (safe for counters)
  snapshot    The data you get back from a read operation
  ref()        Creates a reference to a path in the database
  Query params URL parameters after the ? in a URL
  Pagination  Splitting results into pages (page 1, page 2, ...)
  Bearer token The token sent in Authorization header for auth
  Callable    A Firebase function type that handles auth for you
  Trigger     Code that runs automatically in response to an event
  Cron        A schedule expression (e.g. "0 8 * * *" = every day at 8:00)
